values:
hmm. why do things have to be so difficult. well i looked up to see if i could set up where we went to a red sox game in mid sept, which could happen but i would have to be sure that we could make it and without a vehicle, or gw being able to take some days off i dont think we would be able to. so i found tickets for sept 2nd sunday, game starts at 2pm. so we're just trying to work everything out. should be fun? the casino thing could still work out... if i wanted to put the effort into it. but anyhow... if all fails gw wants a MOSS (pats) jersey so ill get him that from the sports store.&nbsp;
well i have chores to be doing but they just dont seem as fun as just sitting here on the comp. but i do need to get up and clean. of course the living room is always the worst place of all bc natalie always trashes the place. i try to keep up with her and try not to&nbsp;let her throw everything around. my kitchen is spotless. my mom says i have an obsession with cleaning products, which i do. but my kitchen is spotless bc of mr clean wipes... they are like paper towels heavy duty but they disinfect everything which is nice also. but i do need to catch up on some chores that i have been slacking on.&nbsp;
plus natalie is in the stage of being a total terror and i cant take it. i get really annoyed and i yell at her until she sits. she can talk more which is good but then again she says no, and a bunch of other things. nothing naughty just reg no, and i want and such. but she is just not listening to me and then calls me ucky when she cant get her way. and whats even worse she seems to think that she can have a pacifier again just bc her little brother does. i have to hide them, and make sure she doesnt get them or she'll put them in her mouth again. she only tries this trick when im home bc gw would whoop her bum if she did it in front of him. shows how well she listens to me. well its only 1pm and gw works till about 5:30ishpm. i guess he says hes going to try to get the truck tonight but i wouldnt push it if i was him. hes borrowed it a lot and it JUST came out of the shop. i told him he has to be careful. it wouldnt kill us if we didnt have it... his parents would just have to be productive tomorrow and come over here. wow... that would be amazing... his parents actually being productive lol. lazy asses.

hello bitches... lol just wanted to say that. sounds stupid tho. anyhow my day is boring as usuall... even with having 2 beautiful children i think i need some more excitement in my life. well gw wants to go to the mall tonight, guess how? being illegal and driving the car that isnt registered. lol. old habits never die. cant teach a dog new tricks i guess? i really dont think going to mall is that important of taking a chance of getting our car towed or ticketed for like a hudred bucks. but ya know im too bored to say otherwise. i like the silly thrill lol, believe this isnt the worst ive done. i had this mecury, gw bought it for me it was my first car. i drove it with massachusett plates in nh for a while, now the car was registered well not really but the plates were under someone else's name, i didnt know them but was thankful they gave me free plates to ride around on. lasted a while until some pig in manchester, nh decided to give me a ticket for it and then i had to get my car registered in nh. did i mention i had no license this whole time. its funny how we get away with these things huh? good memories, i was lucky.
now my life is boring. well except for the everyday motherhood thing that goes on. and at times its exciting seeing my kids grow into little adults BUT i still need something else going on in my life thats going to be exciting. thats WHY im excited to move to mass, bc im sure there will be something there that will feel that hole. not here though, nothing exciting happens here in maine except for dirty hillbillies moving their shit from one rats nest to another.&nbsp;
errr. gw says hes in a bad mood tonight. sucks, usually this is when we have our juiciest fights. really bad hurtful ones. i guess im just in one of those moods that i think back on all the passed yrs and how fast they flew by. i miss some parts of my life... like when gw and i lived in manchester.... even though it was some fucked up times with us fighting and putting poor p.g. and r.g. through shit... i still made memories with them. i remember how upset i was when gw pushed me to go with him to maryland with his stupid parents. even though i knew i had to leave with him i was so sad. i felt apart of something living there and we had some good times.... even though the bad times were bad and i regret those times i would never give up my good memories.&nbsp;
hmm... i dont know, life just sucks here in maine. so fuckin' boring. the mall is the most exciting place you could say bc there is no where else that is hopping with ppl. well at least normal ppl. everywhere else there are smelly, gross moron ppl. ill say it again ppl from mass/nh NEVER EVER move to maine bc you'll hate it.&nbsp;
oh the red sox lost last night. the first game they won bc they had a double header but the second game they lost. i blame it on gagne, i think hes payed by the yankees to suck at pitching but yeah we blew it. we were 1 point up and then we freakin' blew it. we should have put papelbon up to pitch but NOOOOO terry&nbsp;francona said we couldnt bc he already pitched and we didnt want to tire him out. retard, he actually got thrown out of the game along with youkilis... the ump called a strike when it should have been a ball and they both went crazy... the ump must have been getting butt fucked by jeter and decided to be an ass. yankees suck. we got rid of wily mo pena... he wasnt doing much anyhow.&nbsp; yes mothafucker im a sports freak. had to become one living with gw for so long. now of course ive been a life long red sox fan, my father instilled that in me, he use to take me to ball games as a kid.... BUT i never really understand everything exactly. well now i do though and im getting better. cant wait until the patroits are playing, they had a game last night but it wasnt on tv. pre season game agaisnt the titans. patroits won of course. anyhow we're planning on going to a pats game. that will be fun. im eyeing this pink fleece pats jacket at the sports store along with this pink rain jacket with the red sox logo. there both cute but expensive. hmm gotta go though, gw going to be home soon.
lets hope we sweep the angels tonight. game starts @ 7pm, watch it.

just got back from matthew's doctor's visit... went well. matthew is 17lbs 26 inches long.... big boy and is sooo cute. i can start feeding him mushy foods like potatoes, applesauce and such. im excited, i decided im going to make all homemade baby food for matthew. i didnt do that with natalie i bought store food which is good too, i just thought it would save us money and all the nice farmers markets would have some great veggies and fruits to mash up for him. plus at the same time im supporting our local farmers, how corny do i sound lol. im sooo far from the perfect housewife/perfect mommmy. i just sound like i can fit into that box sometimes, at least i have the ideas and heart. i will deff make my own baby food though and keep nursing matthew. anyone who is thinking of nursing should, it has been the best experience ive had. matthew and i have bonded so well and we are really close and he really thrives off touch and comfort. i nursed my first born for 3 weeks but she wasnt taking as well bc she was so small and didnt have the technique os sucking yet. but forget about it matthew is the ulimate eater lol... hes a good boy. slept with us again last night after i attempted to get him to sleep in his crib :( i was like errr but couldnt resist snuggling with him, i just sleep like a hot dog all night lol. he loves sleeping with us though, likes to be close and comforted... prob all the body heat helps too. it has been a little chilly at night lately, suprising for summer. still have the winter comforter on the bed bc at night it gets chilly maybe thats bc we're next to the ocean and the ocean breeze cools everything down. that is one of the nicer parts of living here is that we're right next to the ocean... oh and the lobster pound was great. i have never been to seafood restuarant that was as great as the lobster pound. and the view was incredible... beautiful right on the ocean... but cold lol :) if my parents ever make their way here ill deff take them to the lobster pound... they will love it.&nbsp; 
well didnt make the post office today :( im sad about that. and with tomorrow being a holiday i dont know when im going to get there. my poor parents are waiting for the picture of the kids. oh and gw's parents left last night. THANK GOD. i guess their in pennsylvania right now keeping on track to MO.&nbsp; im just happy we get to celebreat the 4th without them. i guess there are some parades and such tomorrow that i hope to hit up and see. ill make sure to snap a lot of pics and post them on here. if anyone is interested. :)&nbsp; 
im suddenly extremely tired, did i mention matthew got shots... hes a little grumpy now and in need of some mommy love and comfort.
